Further Analysis.prompt:
The following analyses have been performed for the customer "{company}":

{context}

For any unusual transactions discovered in these analyses, perform an in-depth analysis with further SQL queries to conclude whether or not the flagged transactions are in fact unusual. If one or more analyses failed, retry these analyses. If an analysis returned no results (particularly the recurring payments analysis, there are always recurring payments), assume the queries were incorrect and try again. DO NOT simply provide a summary.

Interim Conclusion.prompt:
The following analyses have been performed for the customer "{company}":

{context}

In one sentence or less, either highlight any unusual transactions that were found, or state that no unusual transactions were found. If any IBAN anomalies were found, please include these in the conclusion.

Interim Conclusion Critique.prompt:
The following analyses have been performed for the customer "{company}":

{context}

Your task is to critically and comprehensively assess the conclusion. If the conclusion states there is an unusual transaction(s), please verify this statement against the data. If the conclusion states there are no unusual transactions, please verify this conclusion against the analysis so far. Be sure to also flag unusual transactions that you think are missing from this conclusion.

Final Conclusion.prompt:
The following analyses have been performed for the customer "{company}":

{context}

In one sentence or less, summarise the above analyses by highlighting any unusual transactions that were found. Do not mention anything other than unusual transactions.

Deep Dive.prompt:
The following analyses have been performed for the customer "{company}":

{context}

Expand on the above final conclusion, providing supporting evidence and explanation for any unusual transactions found into 4 or 5 incredibly short and concise (using shorthand wherever possible) bullet points for each piece of evidence (do not add headers or titles). Make sure to note the time period analysed. Please only expand on the final conclusion and not the previous sub-analyses. Do not talk about normal transactions, only discuss unusual transactions. DO NOT brag about how good the analysis is, but instead provide context. If possible, display a table displaying the unusual transaction(s) with the header 'List of Suspicious Transactions'.
